The two buses, which were heading in opposite directions, collided after the Nairobi-bound bus veered off its lane. The crash happened Thursday morning in the Kiongwani area in eastern Kenya, according to the Daily Nation. Some 62 injured passengers were rushed to hospital for treatment, the local police commander Joseph ole Napeiyan is quoted as saying. Napeiyan also told The Star newspaper that police had managed to control traffic and there was no gridlock on the busy highway. --BBC--